claim.claim-text:
13. A method of preparing a liquid composition comprising silicon dioxide and potassium oxide, the method comprising: 
providing an aqueous solution of potassium silicate comprising silicon dioxide and potassium oxide; 
stirring the aqueous solution with a stirrer at a rotational speed from about 500 rpm to about 5,000 rpm; 
adding hydrosilica gel to the aqueous solution while stirring so that the mole ratio increases beyond about 4.5 without resulting in gelation of the composition.
